                                                                                                                       7                                      Cap raised on suggestion
                      
	New Delhi: The Indian Premier League (IPL) increased the cap for each team to participate in the auction after a suggestion from the Sahara Group chief Subrata Roy, who won Team Pune with a staggering bid of over Rs 1700 crore.         
	Sahara Group chief Roy had suggested that the ceiling should be increased.         
	The IPL on Tuesday said that each team would now be allowed to keep a purse of $7 million (about Rs 35 crore) to bid for players.           (PTI)                                                                                                                 
